To install on Mac OS X

1. check to see what version of python
python --version
python3 --version

2. if don't have python3, need to install xcode
xcode-select --install

3. then install homebrew
/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"

4. and then install python3
brew install python3

5. then install ffmpeg
brew install ffmpeg

6. and then requirements.txt
cd <directory of speech-to-text>
pip3 install -r requirements.txt

Resources
https://wsvincent.com/install-python3-mac/
https://www.alexkras.com/transcribing-audio-file-to-text-with-google-cloud-speech-api-and-python

INSTRUCTIONS ON HOW TO USE
1. open terminal
2. navigate to the speech-to-text directory.  Example command:
cd ""/Users/kfong25/Documents/05Projects/Code/Python/speech-to-text"
4. run the python3 fast.py command against the source directory.  Example:
python3 fast.py "/Users/kfong25/Documents/05Projects/Code/Python/speech-to-text/source"